# AI Assistant Project - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js 14 application with TypeScript that provides an AI assistant with integrations to Google Calendar, Google Tasks, and Notion.

## Key Technologies
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript
- SQLite (better-sqlite3)
- Tailwind CSS
- Vercel AI SDK
- Docker

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript with strict mode
- Prefer functional components
- Use async/await over promises
- Use const/let, never var
- Follow Next.js conventions

## Database
- SQLite is located at data/sqlite/app.db
- All credentials must be encrypted before storage
- Use lib/encryption.ts for encryption/decryption
- Migrations in lib/db/migrate.ts

## Security
- Never commit .env file
- Always encrypt sensitive data before storing
- Use environment variables for secrets
- OAuth tokens must be encrypted

## File Organization
- API routes in app/api/
- Components in app/[page]/
- Utilities in lib/
- Types alongside implementation files

## Development
- Run `bun run dev` for development
- Run `bun run build` for production build
- Run `bun run db:migrate` to update database

## Testing
- Test API routes with curl
- Check health: curl http://localhost:3000/api/health
- Check status: curl http://localhost:3000/api/status
